notes:
I collated some of the information and stories shared with you over the past months into today’s many links. Narratives that were perhaps introduced over several days are here in one place and make for easier investigation.
First are Mount St. Helens’ Six Volcanic Events on May 18, 1980: The Debris Avalanche; Pyroclastic Density Current; Blast Pyroclastic Flows; Plinian Column and Air-Fall Ash; Pumiceous Pyroclastic Flows; and Lahars. 
Second, Mount St. Helens stories: Amazing volcanic processes and people at the mountain.
Third, Mount St. Helens’ Lakes: Bathymetric surveys and chemical analyses of the new and affected lakes, and the race to create outlets.
